<subSubSection pageNumber="722" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="722">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="722">Note:</emphasis>
Although 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kerguélen">Kerguelen</normalizedToken>
(in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="722">Lejeunia</emphasis>
, n.s., 75: 260. 1975) stated &quot;Type: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="…LINN”">...LINN&quot;</normalizedToken>
, this is not accepted as a formal typification, for the reasons explained by Cafferty &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="722">Taxon</emphasis>
49: 240. 2000). Cope (in Nasir &amp; Ali, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="722">Fl. Pakistan</emphasis>
143: 207. 1982) stated that the type was based on a Scheuchzer account but as this is not accompanied by an illustration, it cannot be a type. Meikle (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="722">Fl. Cyprus</emphasis>
2: 1861. 1985) indicated unspecified material in LINN as type but failed to distinguish between sheets 80.7 and 80.13. As they are evidently not part of a single gathering, Art. 9.15 does not apply. Sherif &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Siddiqi’s">Siddiqi's</normalizedToken>
type choice therefore appears to be the earliest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
